items.title: Managing Your Self: Key to Effective Leadership
items.headline: Advanced skills for leaders. Powerful, practical tools that help you build the 'real' teamwork needed to get results.
objectives_summary: How to manage our negative 'knee-jerk' reactions when mistakes are made and things go wrong – so we can keep ourselves, and our team members, focused on solutions. (You will learn a key skill right at the start that you can use immediately to manage challenging situations – both at work and in your personal life – with a lot less stress).
How to correct team members, without demotivating them, when mistakes are made – so they want to keep working enthusiastically with you

How to avoid anger, blame and criticism specifically – in order to prevent their destructive effect on team performance, and your personal performance as well.  (If you’re a road rager, of either the loud or quiet kind, think of this part as ‘Road Rage Rehab.’)

items.title: Social Leadership: My 1st 100 Days

visible_instructors.job_title: Author & Founder at Sea Salt Learning
visible_instructors.name: Julian
visible_instructors.title: Julian Stodd

items.headline: 100 practical activities for becoming a Social Leader
objectives_summary: You will set strong foundations for becoming a Social Leader. Each day consists of an illustration, exploring the topic at hand, some questions, conversations, or activities, and a provocation to take action.  Based around the core principles of the NET model of Social Leadership, the purpose of the course is to guide the early footsteps of your journey.  Every tenth day is an ‘Action Day’, where you are specifically encouraged to put the book down and make a real difference out in your community and team.
